article.headline: Chicago St 74, IUPUI 66
article.story: CHICAGO (AP) -- David Holston scored 17 points while Kevin Jones Jr. scored 13 points and grabbed eight rebounds as Chicago State beat IUPUI 74-66 Thursday night. Nikko Briteramos chipped in 10 points and 11 rebounds off the bench for the Cougars (8-18, 7-8 Mid-Con), who got 30 points from their reserves. George Hill led IUPUI (18-8, 13-2) and all scorers with 22 points on 9-of-15 shooting. David Barlow added 14 for the Jaguars, who couldn't overcome 29.5 percent first-half shooting that saw just three of 13 three-point attempts go down. Chicago State went to the foul line just five times -- scoring twice -- in the first half of the game, but hit 21 of 28 free throws in the second to build on a 27-22 halftime lead.
